Program: Discovery
Title: Memory - part one
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryzd
Last Broadcast Date: 17 May 2005
Exploring the science of memory. The programme looks at the brain processes that make up a memory and the nature of a memory itself. Studio guest is Andrew Mayes, a cognitive neuroscientist. Presenter: Pam Rutherford.